data.chText: 她胳膊给蜜蜂蜇了，肿了起来。
data.enText: Her arm was beginning to swell up where the bee had stung her.
to curve out or make sth curve out
The sails swelled (out) in the wind.
to increase or make sth increase in number or size

data.chText: 去年因生产成本下降，利润有所增加。
data.enText: Last year's profits were swelled by a fall in production costs.

data.chText: 我们期盼有更多的志愿者加入，以壮大目前已在提供帮助的队伍。
data.enText: We are looking for more volunteers to swell the ranks (= increase the number) of those already helping.

data.chText: 欢呼声越来越大，响彻大厅。
data.enText: The cheering swelled through the hall.
to be filled with a strong emotion
the movement of the sea when it rises and falls without the waves breaking
The boat was caught in a heavy (= strong) swell.

data.chText: （尤指身体部位）凸起的形状，鼓出处，隆起处
data.enText: the curved shape of sth, especially a part of the body
the firm swell of her breasts
a situation in which sth increases in size, number, strength, etc.
a gradual increase in the volume of sth

word_means: 凸起的形状，鼓出处，隆起处

means: (尤指身体部位)凸起的形状，鼓出处，隆起处

tr: a crescendo followed by a decrescendo
the undulating movement of the surface of the open sea
a rounded elevation (especially one on an ocean floor)
a man who is much concerned with his dress and appearance

example: The bellies of the starving children are swelling

tr: increase in size, magnitude, number, or intensity
example: The music swelled to a crescendo

tr: come up, as of a liquid
become filled with pride, arrogance, or anger
example: The mother was swelling with importance when she spoke of her son

tr: come up (as of feelings and thoughts, or other ephemeral things)

example: had a great time at the party

value.boxr_value: The forms swelled and swollen are both used as the past participle. swelled 和 swollen 均可用作过去分词。

value.def: If the amount or size of something swells or if something swells it, it becomes larger than it was before.

example.ex: The human population swelled, at least temporarily, as migrants moved south...
example.tran: 随着移居者南移,人口出现膨胀，至少是暂时性膨胀。

example.ex: By the end of this month the size of the mission is expected to swell to 280 people...
example.tran: 到这个月底，参加该任务的人员规模将有望增至 280 人。

example.ex: His bank balance has swelled by £222,000 in the last three weeks...
example.tran: 在过去的 3 周里，他银行的存款多了 222,000 英镑。

example.ex: Offers from other countries should swell the force to 35,000.
example.tran: 其他国家的支援将可使兵力增至 35,000 人。
无家可归者人数的持续增长

example.ex: Its population is swollen by 360,000 refugees.
example.tran: 360,000 名难民使该国人口大增。

value.def: If something such as a part of your body swells, it becomes larger and rounder than normal.

example.ex: Do your ankles swell at night?...
The limbs swell to an enormous size.
When you develop a throat infection or catch a cold the glands in the neck swell up.
example.tran: 当咽喉感染或感冒时，扁桃腺就会肿胀。

value.def: If you swell with a feeling, you are suddenly full of that feeling.

example.ex: She could see her two sons swell with pride.
example.tran: 她能看出她的两个儿子充满了骄傲。
不知从何处响起天籁般的音乐。

value.def: A swell is the regular movement of waves up and down in the open sea.

example.ex: We bobbed gently up and down on the swell of the incoming tide.
example.tran: 我们随着涨潮的浪涌轻轻地起伏。

value.def: You can describe something as swell if you think it is really nice.
value.tran: 极好的;了不起的;非常棒的
